ust of the Desert from my Painted Hobbit Toes and make the long arduous Trek (or ride anyway) to the Island of the Elves.  <BR> I gained Passage on the ship bound to Faydwer, no problem, and watched Freeport fade into the distance beyond the waves.  <BR> It is my amusement, on these long trips, to practice Sneaking and Hiding from view, that in the case of Danger my skill is sufficient. <BR> and so I was thus hidden when a HUGE PAIR OF YELLOW FEET stormed into veiw and down the length of the ship! a giant and fearsome Cyclops had boarded the ship and began to kill all those on board!  <BR> shaking and thankfully hidden, I ducked under the growing pile of corpses. soon everyone on the boat was dead except me. the cyclops glared around, and, seeing no more prey, jumped off the side. the corpses littered around me gave a shudder as we left the ocean of tears, and fell off the boat into the deeps.  <BR> calling out for any form of life, I found the only other survivor-- another rogue, who had also hidden prior to the attack. <BR> its times like this when a Rogue is happy to be alive and who she is. <BR>  <BR>    <p>Jete D'PaintedToes
of the Jesters
of Tarew Marr
